  "A local government is deciding whether to allow a mining company to operate near a river that provides drinking water. To make an informed decision, they consult geologists, ecologists, economists, and public health experts. This approach demonstrates:": "",
  "That only geologists should make environmental decisions": "",
  "That science should not inform government decisions": "",
  "An unnecessary waste of time and resources": "",
