  "A team studying ocean acidification includes a marine biologist, an atmospheric chemist, an economist, and a policy analyst. The biologist studies coral reef decline, the chemist measures CO2 absorption, the economist calculates fishery losses, and the policy analyst drafts emission regulations. This team structure shows that:": "",
